steak knives and other super pointy stuff. Besides, only three compartment? You\u0027ll have to mix up the big and little spoons. Anyways, my dishwasher has six smaller cutlery slots, which we also use for small plastic lids...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-31T07:00:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFrom some old game, a masculinity test or so.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u0022Where do you put the forks and the spoons?\u0022\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u0022They fall where I throw them to, entering the kitchen.\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Lewie","CreatedById":203745,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-31T16:33:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLoud, obnoxious chewing and people that make a mess and expect you to clean it up.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HansonKerman","CreatedById":185809,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-31T16:37:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223794715\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022194293\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221590942823\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022203745\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Lewie\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, Lewie said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPeople that make a mess and expect you to clean it up.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Lucida Sans Unicode\u0027, \u0027Lucida Grande\u0027, sans-serif;\u0022\u003E*trembles in anger*\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Lucida Sans Unicode\u0027, \u0027Lucida Grande\u0027, sans-serif;\u0022\u003Eholy frick i hate that\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RealKerbal3x","CreatedById":183830,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-31T18:33:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhenever someone spells (or says) \u0027a lot\u0027 as \u0027alot\u0027 a small part of me dies inside.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"StrandedonEarth","CreatedById":89439,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-31T19:03:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTeenage sons that deliberately break rules\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:mad:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022105.88\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_angry.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:mad:\u0022 width=\u002217\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-31T20:01:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223794801\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022194293\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221590949981\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022183830\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022RealKerbal3x\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, RealKerbal3x said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhenever someone spells (or says) \u0027a lot\u0027 as \u0027alot\u0027 a small part of me dies inside.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u0027s an easy fix for that.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://hyperboleandahalf.blogspot.com/2010/04/alot-is-better-than-you-at-everything.html\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://hyperboleandahalf.blogspot.com/2010/04/alot-is-better-than-you-at-everything.html\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"IncongruousGoat","CreatedById":157062,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-31T20:53:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is going to be crazy levels of nitpicky, but CGI rocket exhaust plumes in film. They\u0027re nearly always depicted as the big, opaque, cloudy exhaust typical of solid motors, even when the rocket in question is very clearly liquid-fueled. I can let it slide if the film in question isn\u0027t depicting a real rocket for which good reference footage is available (e.g. the MAV from \u003Cem\u003EThe Martian\u003C/em\u003E)... but if it\u0027s a historical film? No. Just NO. There is \u003Cem\u003ENO\u003C/em\u003E valid excuse for getting that wrong. All the reference footage you could ever want is available for free on the Internet, and it\u0027s trivial to look at that footage and observe what the plume \u0026amp; exhaust are supposed to look like. \u003Cem\u003EThis is not something that\u0027s difficult to get right\u003C/em\u003E. And yet, movie after movie gets this wrong.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGAH. Drives me completely nuts.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-31T21:38:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223793736\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022194293\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221590844847\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022144985\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022XB-70A\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 5/30/2020 at 9:20 AM, XB-70A said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPeople who are unable to properly store cutlery in a dishwasher,\u00A0which means in their respective racks and in the right position. The vast majority of dishwashers (even entry-level) come with three compartments;\u00A0one for each isn\u0027t that logic?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSee in my experience the best way to get a whole load of unwashed spoons is to put them in the same tray. They stick together and cause all manner of problems. So, I do the exact opposite of what you find logical and so have clean spoons spread through the 5 slots, with other silverware between them.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TheSaint","CreatedById":70033,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-31T22:14:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223794812\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022194293\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221590951806\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002289439\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022StrandedonEarth\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, StrandedonEarth said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTeenage sons that deliberately break rules\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:mad:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022105.88\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_angry.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:mad:\u0022 width=\u002217\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI thought that\u0027s what they were for? Teenage sons break the rules, teenage daughters throw tantrums and give you sass. The root purpose of both is to keep Jim Beam and Hair Club for Men in business.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbart","CreatedById":78303,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-31T23:03:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOoooh, where to stop? Hahaha. Here\u0027s a few that are related to online-forums:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nWriting words that are not an acronym or abbreviation in ALL CAPS. (\u0022\u003Cem\u003EI prefer saving my camera images in RAW format\u0022\u003C/em\u003E)\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nWhile on the subject, calling each abbreviation an acronym. It doesn\u0027t trigger me anymore, just annoys me. NASA is an acronym. PDF is not.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nUnnecessary use of \u003Cem\u003Esome\u003C/em\u003E form of mathematical representation when not necessary, ie. writing 6.67\u00D710\u003Csup\u003E-11\u003C/sup\u003E as 6.67*10^-11 or I\u003Csub\u003Esp\u003C/sub\u003E as \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Specific Impulse (rocketry) or Internet Service Provider\u0022\u003EISP\u003C/abbr\u003E. This forum supports the proper formatting, is it really that hard to use it?\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"XB-70A","CreatedById":144985,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-31T23:33:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223794895\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022194293\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221590961129\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Superfluous J\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Superfluous J said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSee in my experience the best way to get a whole load of unwashed spoons is to put them in the same tray. They stick together and cause all manner of problems. So, I do the exact opposite of what you find logical and so have clean spoons spread through the 5 slots, with other silverware between them.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t have\u00A0them sticking together. Potentially because I put forks and spoons bottom first, so they tend to disperse. Knives are going head first, however. It\u0027s just safer to grab them this way.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HansonKerman","CreatedById":185809,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-06-01T00:13:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223794870\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022194293\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221590958421\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022157062\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022IncongruousGoat\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, IncongruousGoat said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is going to be crazy levels of nitpicky, but CGI rocket exhaust plumes in film. They\u0027re nearly always depicted as the big, opaque, cloudy exhaust typical of solid motors, even when the rocket in question is very clearly liquid-fueled. I can let it slide if the film in question isn\u0027t depicting a real rocket for which good reference footage is available (e.g. the MAV from \u003Cem\u003EThe Martian\u003C/em\u003E)... but if it\u0027s a historical film? No. Just NO. There is \u003Cem\u003ENO\u003C/em\u003E valid excuse for getting that wrong. All the reference footage you could ever want is available for free on the Internet, and it\u0027s trivial to look at that footage and observe what the plume \u0026amp; exhaust are supposed to look like. \u003Cem\u003EThis is not something that\u0027s difficult to get right\u003C/em\u003E. And yet, movie after movie gets this wrong.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGAH. Drives me completely nuts.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Lucida Sans Unicode\u0027, \u0027Lucida Grande\u0027, sans-serif;\u0022\u003EPretty nit picky but now I think about it it\u2019s so true. Listen: (I\u2019m not the most educated of people but to my knowledge):\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Lucida Sans Unicode\u0027, \u0027Lucida Grande\u0027, sans-serif;\u0022\u003Eliquid fuel: generally not as much *boooom omg\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EFIRE FARTS\u003C/strong\u003E*. And in space, it\u2019s just some flame swirling around the bell. It\u2019s easy to find footage. Do historical films not do that? Never watched one. But if they don\u2019t:\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Lucida Sans Unicode\u0027, \u0027Lucida Grande\u0027, sans-serif;\u0022\u003Eseriously.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Lucida Sans Unicode\u0027, \u0027Lucida Grande\u0027, sans-serif;\u0022\u003Ebruh.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Lucida Sans Unicode\u0027, \u0027Lucida Grande\u0027, sans-serif;\u0022\u003Eget it right.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RoninFrog","CreatedById":203049,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-06-01T03:39:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen people split the rocket using a TVR adapter and then \u0022join\u0022 it back together using another one.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAAAAAAAAAHHH!!\u00A0 Only ONE of those nodes is actually connected, dude!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s so\u00A0terrible because it looks symmetrical but you know it\u0027s really not.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-06-01T06:48:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223